  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: Self
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Nahal's Reckless Dweomer
@60055 = ~Wand of Nahal's Reckless Dweomer~
@60056 = ~The Wild Mage's ultimate last-resort, a wild surge is purposefully invoked; the result might be beneficial to the wielder, or it might be completely disastrous: this is the risk taken in casting Nahal's Reckless Dweomer.

When activated, select a known spell to attempt to cast; the wand releases a sudden flood of wild magical energy. The Wild Mage hopes to seize and shape that energy into a desired spell effect. The attempt usually fails, but something almost always occurs in the process -- the actual effect of the wand is determined randomly by a dice roll on the Wild Surge Table (see the manual for more details).

Because the release of energy is planned, the wand's caster level (%magnitude%) is added to the dice roll. If the result indicates success, then the magical energy is shaped into the desired effect. More often than not, the effect is completely unexpected.

STATISTICS:
(Wild Magic)

Charge abilities:
– Nahal's Reckless Dweomer
  – Pick a known spell
  – Wild surge occurs that attempts to cast the selected spell
  Range: Special
  Duration: Special
  Area of Effect: Special
  Saving Throw: Special

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Spook
@60057 = ~Wand of Spook~
@60058 = ~This wand's effect plays upon natural fears to cause the target creature to perceive the wielder as someone or something inimical, which then appears to advance upon it in a threatening manner. If the creature does not make a successful save vs. Wand (with a penalty of %magnitude%), it turns and flees at maximum speed as far from the wielder as possible. Although the caster does not actually pursue the fleeing creature, a phantasm from its own mind does. Undead are completely unaffected.

STATISTICS:
(Illusion/Phantasm)

Charge abilities:
– Spook
  – Target flees at maximum speed as far from the wielder as possible
  Range: 30 ft.
  Duration: 3 rounds
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: Saving vs. Wand (%magnitude% penalty) negates

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Dancing Lights
@60059 = ~Wand of Dancing Lights~
@60060 = ~This wand creates up to four glowing spheres of light (such as evidenced by will-o-wisps) or one faintly glowing, vaguely humanoid shape, somewhat similar to a fire elemental. The dancing lights move randomly without concentration upon such movement by the wielder. Although the lights cause no physical harm, they can distract enemies until either their duration expires or dispersed by weapon or magic.

STATISTICS:
(Alteration)

